    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Parent's Role</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Will Meyer letter emphasizes parent's role in determining what movies their children will see (Sept 18 letter)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>A Sept. 18 letter writer decries the practice by movie studios of including action figures of characters in PG-13 movies with children's meals at fast-food restaurants. He says this practice is ''extraordinarily effective at increasing a child's wish to see a movie'' that is not appropriate for his or her age.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>A Sept. 18 letter writer decries the practice by movie studios of including action figures of characters in PG-13 movies with children's meals at fast-food restaurants. He says this practice is ''extraordinarily effective at increasing a child's wish to see a movie'' that is not appropriate for his or her age.</p>
        <p>Placing candy in the checkout line at my local supermarket is also extraordinarily effective at increasing my son's wish to eat candy that is not appropriate for his teeth. My equally effective response as a parent to his request is to say ''no.''</p>
        <p>WILL MEYER  Clifton, Va., Sept. 18, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
